Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class SearchCategory<T extends AbstractComponent>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.Category<T>
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.SearchCategory<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the AbstractComponent type that is the common ancestor for all of the concrete component types referenced by this search category. This ancestor is used by methods such as findByIdent(AbstractModel, int) and findByCC(AbstractModel, int).
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable
    public class SearchCategory<T extends AbstractComponent>
extends Category<T>
    A virtual search-only category with child categories. Search categories can be used to retrieve and display components but do not appear in the category hierarchy for any model or plug-in. For example, the set of 1-dimensional hydraulic components in a plug-in that has both 1D and 3D hydraulic components.

    Warning: Search categories should only be used in plug-ins that also use the built-in ComponentSet to manage their lists of components.

    See Also:
    ComponentSet
